verbose_text: Just as cigarette smoke has been shown to increase the number of IL-17A + NKT cells in the lung, alternative cellular sources of IL-17A include NK cells and gammadelta-T cells which have been shown to become potent producers of IL-17A upon cigarette smoke exposure, with the frequency of IL-17 + gammadelta-T cells significantly increasing in number.
evidence: smoke has been shown to increase the number of IL-17A
